column5: Got out with FishnSled last week, launched outta Whitby for an after work evening fish. Shore temps were stupid hot, but it was quite nice on the lake. After the five mile run out, pretty quiet until an 8 lb Rainbow hit the rigger. Stayed quiet until we decided to start trolling in as it was getting late. Triple header of Chinnies made for a few minutes of chaos. One spit the hook and the other two made it to the boat. Was a blast and looking forward to our next trip! For some unknown reason I can't post the pic right side up! HH
